I'm so excited to finally be able to post this collab with a guy who I consider like a brother @ekaglass 

We started the prep for this tube over a year ago and finally had a chance to assemble it.

The fire to jail bird pull was made by myself using the last of my illuminate for the stringers.

The sections are all rewigged by eka and the rhino splash guard and scorpion.

The Galaxy disc perc functions like a beast, creating those tiny little bubbles my tubes have become famous for its very airy with little restrictions.

The worked joint is 18mm, and the tube comes with an 18/4 slide with scorpion tail and rhino horn.

It always amazes me what we come up with each time we get together to create amazing pieces like these.

This tube is definitely a 1 of 1, and we will never be duplicating this again. 

If you think you're special enough to own this piece of art, please reach out  to eka or myself. 

Thanks as always for all the support, and thank you, eka, for always having my back.

Always a pleasure getting down and pushing the limits with my brotha @titzglass . He's always entertained my ridiculous ideas and we both just go in do or die most of the time 😂

This 12" Caiman skull with matching 18mm Caiman slide, featuring a 30 hole stem and Mystery Adventurine for teeth and accents, was a challenge to say the least lol. There is a slight imperfection in the angle one of the jaws is placed. It's purely an aesthetic issue however hit up either of us a for a sick deal because of it 💪

This will be our last available collab before my show end of year where Jaime and I have something ridiculous in store for u all. Thx for all the love and support 💕

This doesn't mean I am not doing other styles of tubes. Just the disco king is what I want to put my attention to.
